{"id": "EUVD-2022-55176", "enisaUuid": "602cb69d-2b1c-39e0-88ad-8b14ed2101bc", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nerofs/zmap.c: Fix incorrect offset calculation\n\nEffective offset to add to length was being incorrectly calculated,\nwhich resulted in iomap->length being set to 0, triggering a WARN_ON\nin iomap_iter_done().\n\nFix that, and describe it in comments.\n\nThis was reported as a crash by syzbot under an issue about a warning\nencountered in iomap_iter_done(), but unrelated to erofs.\n\nC reproducer: https://syzkaller.appspot.com/text?tag=ReproC&x=1037a6b2880000\nKernel config: https://syzkaller.appspot.com/text?tag=KernelConfig&x=e2021a61197ebe02\nDashboard link: https://syzkaller.appspot.com/bug?extid=a8e049cd3abd342936b6", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T18:31:24", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-29T18:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2144859229c1e74f52d3ea067338d314a83a8afb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9f31d8c889d9a4e47bfcc6c4537d0c9f89fe582c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6acd87d50998ef0afafc441613aeaf5a8f5c9eff", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49747"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49747"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0771af2b-3fdc-33b8-82db-3cb52ee9555c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "0cfe9b8b-6576-3790-a8dc-ac9e5b792abe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": ""}, {"id": "3b147a83-31e6-3d70-b83e-e158309cf7ab", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <2144859229c1e74f52d3ea067338d314a83a8afb"}, {"id": "4b7f2851-c59d-3bab-a675-104a05fda7cb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "eadcd6b5a1eb39866ab8d8a3e4f2e51bc51a2350 <6acd87d50998ef0afafc441613aeaf5a8f5c9eff"}, {"id": "4ce20d69-bec7-341a-8556-7cf3b5f78276", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <9f31d8c889d9a4e